zachary.shapes

Class Rectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • zachary.shapes.Shape
      • zachary.shapes.Shape2D
        • zachary.shapes.Rectangle

  • public class Rectangle
extends Shape2D
    This class represents a double precision rectangle, that draws a rectangle and can calculate basic properties of the rectangle, such as finding the area or perimeter.
    Version:
    10/9/18
    Author:
    Zachary Wang

      • draw

        public void draw(processing.core.PApplet marker)
        Draws a new instance of a Rectangle object with the left and right edges of the rectangle at x and x + width. The top and bottom edges are at y and y + height.
        Overrides:
        draw in class Shape2D
        Parameters:
        marker - the reference of the PApplet used to draw the rectangle
        Precondition:
        marker must not be null, and appropriate settings should have been selected (color, fill, etc)
        Postcondition:
        the marker will have its rectangle mode modified to PApplet.CORNER
